org.ow2.proactive.scripting

Class Script<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ow2.proactive.scripting.Script<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - Template class's type of the result.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FlowScript, ForkEnvironmentScript, SelectionScript, SimpleScript, TaskScript

    @PublicAPI
public abstract class Script<E>
extends Object
implements Serializable
    A simple script to evaluate using java 6 scripting API.
    Since:
    ProActive Scheduling 0.9

      • fetchScript

        public String fetchScript()
        If the script is defined by an url, in fetchImmediately=false mode, retrieve and return the script content from the url. The script internal definition will not be modified, thus allowing fetching again the url prior to execution. Otherwise, return the inline script definition
        Returns:
        the script, or null if the script could not be downloaded from the provided url.

      • fetchScriptWithExceptionHandling

        public String fetchScriptWithExceptionHandling()
                                        throws IOException
        If the script is defined by an url, in fetchImmediately=false mode, retrieve and return the script content from the url. The script internal definition will not be modified, thus allowing fetching again the url prior to execution. Otherwise, return the inline script definition
        Returns:
        the script.
        Throws:
        IOException - when the script cannot be accessed
